Season the chicken with salt and pepper. Place a slice of chicken diagonally across the spring roll pastry.Lay 6 prawns on top of the chicken slice. Top with two to three chilli strips and a handful of coriander.Place another slice of chicken over the coriander.Fold in ends of pastry and roll up in an envelope shape. Secure with a cocktail stick.Deep-fry the chicken and prawn rolls in hot oil until golden brown and cooked through, about 2-3 minutes.  Do not have oil too hot or the rolls will brown before the filling is cooked through.Drain on absorbent kitchen towels.Remove cocktail stick from each roll.